CAAL Tool Registry License v1.0

Copyright (c) 2026 CoreWorxLab and Contributors

1. Definitions

"Registry" — The collective contents of the caal-tools repository, including
all workflows, manifests, documentation, and index files.

"Tool" — An individual workflow and its associated files (manifest, README,
icon) contributed to the Registry.

"Contributor" — The original author of a Tool, as identified in the Tool's
manifest.

"CAAL-Compatible System" — Any voice assistant or automation platform that
integrates with the Registry for non-commercial, personal use.

"Commercial Use" — Selling, licensing, or otherwise monetizing the Registry or
its Tools as part of a product or service, including offering the Registry as a
hosted service for paying customers.

"CoreWorxLab" — The maintainer and operator of the CAAL project and the
Registry.

2. Grant of Rights

Permission is granted, free of charge, to any person to:

a. Use Tools from the Registry for personal, non-commercial purposes with any
   CAAL-Compatible System.

b. Modify Tools for personal use or to contribute improvements back to the
   Registry.

c. Share individual Tools with attribution to the original Contributor and
   CoreWorxLab.

3. Contributor Rights

a. Contributors retain full ownership and rights to the Tools they submit.

b. Contributors may use, modify, relicense, publish, or commercialize their own
   Tools independently, without restriction.

c. By submitting a Tool to the Registry, Contributors grant CoreWorxLab a
   non-exclusive, perpetual, irrevocable license to:
   - Distribute the Tool as part of the Registry
   - Include the Tool in CoreWorxLab products and services
   - Modify, adapt, or integrate the Tool as needed for CoreWorxLab's offerings

d. This grant does not transfer ownership. Contributors can withdraw future
   versions of their Tools from the Registry at any time, but CoreWorxLab
   retains rights to versions already submitted.

4. Restrictions on Third Parties

a. No Commercial Use of the Registry by Third Parties. The Registry, in whole
   or in substantial part, may not be used commercially by anyone other than
   CoreWorxLab without prior written permission. This includes but is not
   limited to:
   - Bundling the Registry with a competing commercial product
   - Offering the Registry as a hosted or managed service
   - Reselling or sublicensing access to the Registry
   - Forking the Registry to power a competing tool marketplace

b. No Misrepresentation. The Registry or its Tools may not be presented as the
   work of anyone other than the original Contributors and CoreWorxLab.

c. Attribution Required. Any permitted use of the Registry or individual Tools
   must include:
   - Credit to the original Contributor (by GitHub username)
   - Credit to CoreWorxLab as the Registry maintainer
   - A link to the original Registry repository

5. No Warranty

THE REGISTRY AND ITS TOOLS ARE PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND,
EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. IN NO EVENT SHALL COREWORXLAB OR CONTRIBUTORS BE LIABLE FOR
ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM USE OF THE REGISTRY.

6. Commercial Licensing for Third Parties

For third-party commercial use inquiries, contact CoreWorxLab at
cmac@coreworxlab.com.
